 Resolved resonance parameter evaluation for Cr-53 was done with  2434 1451
the computer code SAMMY.[La03] Capture and transmission           2434 1451
measurements enriched Cr-53 and natural chromium were performed   2434 1451
at the Oak Ridge Electron Linear Accelerator (ORELA) of the Oak   2434 1451
Ridge National Laboratory. The neutron transmission and capture   2434 1451
data were measured in the energy range from 10 keV to 600 keV.    2434 1451
The transmission data were measured at the 80-meter flight-path,  2434 1451
whereas the 40-meter flight-path was used for the capture cross   2434 1451
section measurements. The determination of the resolved resonance 2434 1451
parameters for the chromium isotope below 100 keV relied mainly   2434 1451
on the recent ORELA measurements. The ORELA capture cross section 2434 1451
data were essential in the evaluation since there are no capture  2434 1451
cross section data available in the literature. In                2434 1451
addition to the new ORELA measurements, existing high-resolution  2434 1451
transmission data for enriched nuclides were also included in the 2434 1451
evaluation. Thermal cross section data available in the EXFOR data2434 1451
system were also included in the evaluation.                      2434 1451
                                                                  2434 1451
 Direct-semidirect (DSD) capture on Cr-53 was computed using the  2434 1451
computer code CUPIDO created by F.S. Dietrich (LLNL).[Pa95]  To   2434 1451
obtain the optical potential for this computation, the global     2434 1451
optical potential of Koning-Delaroche was manually adjusted to    2434 1451
reproduce the experimentally measured scattering radius R'.       2434 1451
This method was justified since low-energy phenomena are          2434 1451
determined by R'.  It was found that the low-energy capture is    2434 1451
dominated by electric-dipole (E1) capture of s-wave neutrons.  A  2434 1451
density form of the E1 operator was used.  The spectroscopic      2434 1451
factors for the capturing bound states in Cr-54 were taken from   2434 1451
W. Gongqing.[ND87] The computed thermal DSD capture is about 0.32 2434 1451
barns.  The uncertainty of DSD computation is inherently large,   2434 1451
usually about 20-30%.                                             2434 1451
                                                                  2434 1451
 A set of resonance parameter describing the experimental data    2434 1451
was obtained. Resonance parameter covariance matrices were also   2434 1451
obtained in the SAMMY evaluation process. The Cr-53 evaluation was2434 1451
done in the energy region 10-5 eV 564 keV.                        2434 1451
